  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>General</Type>
    <Text>This hotel has been totally refurbished during 2008 and 2009, having been finalized only in Spring 2009. Hence all the facilities are brand new, and so are the decorations. This is an excellent hotel located in the heart of London's West End, and it comes highly recommended.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>SurroundingArea</Type>
    <Text>The hotel is situated in the heart of Central London, in the West End, just two minutes walk from Tottenham Court Road Station. The hotel is situated close to Oxford and Bond Street and convenient to Covent Garden and Theatreland.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>RoomTypes</Type>
    <Text>All rooms are luxuriously decorated, and contemporary modern in style, and have all been just refurbished during 2009,designed to provide every comfort and feature to meet the needs of all guests.The rooms are very large for London standards, and all feature a long list of facilities.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>PropertyInformation</Type>
    <Text>This is a grand period building with a double staircase entrance, a landmark of the area.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>DiningFacilities</Type>
    <Text>The hotel has one restaurant "Lutyens" which offers contemporary British cuisine. The club-like Lutyens bars with its rich wooden panels and relaxed atmosphere is a welcome retreat at the end of the day.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>Short</Type>
    <Text>The lobby is large in size with lofty ceilings and tall windows. It is decorated in dark and light wood and has plenty of sofas and chairs for guests to use. Mixing modern design and period features, the lobby style appeals to all types of guests and tastes.</Text>
  </Description>
